

*******************************************************************************
				COOKIES
*******************************************************************************

https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Cookies

Small piece of data that a server sends to the user's web browser.
Browser may store it and send it back with next request to the same server.
Used to tell if two requests came from the same browser
	To keeping a user logged-in, for example.
It remembers stateful information for the stateless HTTP protocol.


Session management
    Logins, shopping carts, game scores, ...
Personalization
    User preferences, themes, and other settings
Tracking
    Recording and analyzing user behavior 

The Set-Cookie HTTP response header sends cookies from the server to the user
	agent. A simple cookie is set like this:
		Set-Cookie: <cookie-name>=<cookie-value>; Expires=Wed, 21 Oct 2015
			07:28:00 GMT; Secure; HttpOnly; SameSite=Strict

https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Tools/Storage_Inspector
https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Web_Storage_API
https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/IndexedDB_API


























